        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-02-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <head>5. Memorandum From Acting Director of Central Intelligence <persName
                        corresp="#p_KE_2">Knoche</persName> to the President’s Assistant for
                    National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_BZ_1"
                        >Brzezinski</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d5fn1">Source:
                        Carter Library, National Security Affairs, Staff Material, Middle East File,
                        Chron File, Box 130, <persName corresp="#p_QWB_1">Quandt</persName>:
                        2/4–9/77. Secret; Sensitive.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-02-08">February 8, 1977</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Interest of <gloss target="#t_PLO_1">PLO</gloss> Chairman <persName
                            corresp="#p_AY_2">Yasir ’Arafat</persName> in Establishing a Dialogue
                        with the United States Government</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. The following information was obtained on 2 February 1977 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >1½ lines not declassified</hi>] Palestine Liberation Organization (<gloss
                        target="#t_PLO_1">PLO</gloss>) Chairman <persName corresp="#p_AY_2">Yasir
                        ‘Arafat</persName> is seeking ways of establishing a dialogue with United
                    States Government officials but is uncertain about how to accomplish this. On
                        [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>] January 1977,
                        ‘<persName corresp="#p_AY_2">Arafat</persName> discussed the problem in
                    Beirut [<hi rend="italic">6 lines not declassified</hi>] ‘<persName
                        corresp="#p_AY_2">Arafat</persName> expressed interest in having [<hi
                        rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] contact you to discuss ways in
                    which a dialogue could be established. ‘<persName corresp="#p_AY_2"
                        >Arafat</persName> indicated that the idea for a dialogue originated with
                    Egyptian President <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Anwar Al-Sadat</persName>.</p>
                <p>2. This information is also being provided to the Secretary of State, The
                    Honorable <persName corresp="#p_VC_1">Cyrus R. Vance</persName>. No other
                    dissemination is being made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KE_2">
                            <hi rend="strong">E. H. Knoche</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
